          "2b_score": 4,
          "2b_reason": "Counts are generally followable with directions and body parts, but several parts are not fully executable as written: “quarter-beat stops transitioning” lacks a concrete count subdivision plan; “head isolation points on 58 and 60 a beats” is unclear (which direction/shape/stop quality); several descriptions rely on musical adjectives (“maximum intensity”, “captures riser”) rather than specifying exact actions on each count/subcount.",
          "2c_score": 3,
          "2c_reason": "Some transitions are plausible (Scooby Doo into point/lock, groove to locks), but multiple back-to-back direction changes plus rapid travel then immediate lock stacks (e.g., 49-52 full diagonal travel into rapid Which-a-way with point accents; 61-64 escalating speed with syncopated locks including jump lock) risk being physically cramped at 115 BPM without prep counts. Bridge acceleration conceptually works but the stated subdivision changes can feel abrupt/unworkable in pure Locking timing.",
          "3a_score": 4,
